# Proposal PDF & Link Page Improvements

Based on the feedback received, I've analyzed what's already implemented vs. what's missing. Below is a focused plan covering the **high-impact improvements** that will noticeably improve conversion and polish.

## What's Already Done (No Changes Needed)
- ✅ Pricing table with zebra rows and totals
- ✅ Services included section
- ✅ Timeline section  
- ✅ Terms & conditions / Notes sections
- ✅ Client acceptance + signature blocks
- ✅ Quotation validity section
- ✅ Discussion/comments on link page
- ✅ Approve button (sticky CTA) on link page

## What Needs Improvement

---

### 1. PDF Templates (`src/lib/templates.ts`)

#### A. Upgrade Signature Area — Add Date Fields + "Digitally Generated" Note
The current signature area is minimal — just a line and name. Upgrade to include:
- Date fields alongside each signature line
- A "Digitally generated proposal" note below signatures

#### B. Payment Terms → Visual Milestone Table  
The current `payment_terms` is rendered as plain text. When payment terms contain milestone-style data like "50/25/25", it's easy to miss. Add a **structured payment milestone mini-table** in the PDF using the same data format (3-row table with milestone name, percentage, and trigger).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Since payment terms are stored as freeform text in the DB, we can't auto-parse them into a table. Instead, I'll add a visual **payment milestones** section to the `buildBody` function that uses structured `payment_milestones` data (which already exists in the DB after approval). For the PDF (which is generated pre-approval), I'll parse common patterns like "Advance: 50%, Mid: 25%, Final: 25%" from the payment_terms text and render them in a mini-table format. If the text doesn't match a known pattern, it falls back to the current plain text display.

#### C. Footer Branding Simplification
Current: `"Generated with Kalvora | Powered by KALVORA"` — repetitive.  
Change to: `"[Studio Name] · kalvora.kaliprlabs.in"` — one clean brand line + website.

#### D. Tighten Vertical Rhythm
Reduce some of the large empty gaps between sections. Use a consistent spacing scale (12px between sections, 4px internal).

#### E. Improve Pricing Table Emphasis
- Slightly stronger row separators
- Bold only key numbers (subtotal, tax, total)
- Softer zebra background

#### F. Increase Label Contrast (Luxury Template)
Gold-on-light-gray labels in the luxury template are low contrast when printed. Darken the gold slightly and increase font weight.

#### G. Reorder Header Hierarchy
Feedback says: Project + client → Deliverables snapshot → Price summary → CTA. The "Prepared By" section should be less dominant.  
Change: Move "Prepared By" details to smaller text, make client + project info more prominent at top.

#### H. Add Scope Snapshot Card
Add a tight card showing:
- Included: X services
- Timeline: start + duration
- Rooms: count

This reduces back-and-forth and supports the "faster close" positioning.

---

### 2. Public Link Page (`src/app/view/[id]/page.tsx`)

#### A. Add "Next Step" Action Block Under Total
Currently the link page shows total cost but is passive. Add an action block under the total:
- ✅ Approve online (the existing sticky button, but also an inline card)
- 💬 Request changes (scroll to discussion)
- 📱 Talk on WhatsApp (link to designer's phone via wa.me)

#### B. Add Scope Snapshot Card  
Same as the PDF improvement — add a tight summary card showing services count, room count, and timeline on the link page.

#### C. Simplify Footer Branding
Same as PDF — remove the duplicate "Powered by Kalvora" text. Keep one clean line.

---

### 3. Invoice Page (`src/app/invoice/[id]/page.tsx`)

#### A. Footer Branding Simplification  
Same treatment — remove repetitive branding, keep one line + website.

---

